                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.032/9.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 130.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quinto</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that on Saturday,
                    August 10, the Ecuadorian Congress assembled in regular session for the year
                    1912. Dr. Alfredo Baquerizo Moreno was elected President of the Senate and
                    according to the Constitution will be acting President until September first,
                    1912, when General Plaza will assume the office.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rutherford Bingham</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
